          <actionDate>2018-02-27</actionDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Second Amendment For Every Registrable Voter Act or the SAFER Voter Act</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to modify age restrictions on the sale or delivery of a firearm by a federally licensed gun dealer, manufacturer, importer, or collector. </p> <p>Currently, it is unlawful for a licensee to sell or deliver: (1) any firearm to an individual less than 18 years of age, or (2) a handgun to an individual less than 21 years of age. </p> <p>This bill eliminates the prohibition on sale or delivery of a handgun to an individual less than 21 years of age.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
